nd present the facts.","pct":38}],"Science":[{"grade":"Grade 8","skill":"Simple techniques will be introduced to extract answers from asked questions. For instance, how to identify substances derived from colored flowers and how to determine whether green leaves contain chlorophyll.","pct":27},{"grade":"Grade 8","skill":"Preparing and explaining graphical data, for instance, plotting distance against time graphs.","pct":28},{"grade":"Grade 8","skill":"This involves creating and interpreting diagrams, such as anatomical diagrams of humans and plants, as well as preparation for experiments.","pct":32},{"grade":"Grade 8","skill":"Discussing the story of scientific discoveries and selecting important ones.","pct":33},{"grade":"Grade 8","skill":"Measure the angle of incidence and angle of reflection","pct":35},{"grade":"Grade 8","skill":"This involves relating processes and events to their causes. Examples include the relationship between wind speed and air pressure, various soil types and crop production, and the impact of groundwater depletion on human activities.","pct":38}],"Maths":[{"grade":"Grade 8","skill":"Analyze data from the column chart, comparing seasonal strengths between summer and winter and other relevant observations based on collected data.","pct":31},{"grade":"Grade 8","skill":"Calculate the volume of a product from the two ends of a triangular region and fix the volume of the third side.","pct":36}],"SST":[{"grade":"Grade 8","skill":"Explain the causes of forest fires, landslides, man-made disasters, and ways to mitigate disasters.","pct":21},{"grade":"Grade 8","skill":"Explain about the main crops, different types of farming, and various agricultural activities in their region.","pct":36}]},"top":{"Odia":[{"grade":"Grade 8","skill":"Use correct grammar in framing sentences in Language use appropriate word to frame sentences","pct":83},{"grade":"Grade 5","skill":"Read other materials alongside your textbook (such as children literature, main news articles, magazines, posters, etc.) and gain an understanding of them.","pct":78},{"grade":"Grade 5","skill":"Explain the meanings of unfamiliar words from word lists","pct":76}],"EVS":[{"grade":"Grade 5","skill":"Identify specific characteristics, such as shape (head, limbs, teeth, skin surface), habitat (whether domesticated or wild), fruits, vegetables, and spices, along with their life cycles, uses (such as for food, medicine, decoration, etc.), and sensory attributes (such as smell, taste, preferences).","pct":76}],"Maths":[{"grade":"Grade 8","skill":"Determine the factors, prime factors, cube, and cube roots of the given numbers.","pct":88},{"grade":"Grade 5","skill":"Understand, identify, and extend geometric patterns based on symmetry.","pct":76},{"grade":"Grade 5","skill":"Recognize the structure of multiplication and division up to the 9-times table.","pct":75}],"SST":[{"grade":"Grade 8","skill":"Discuss the factors affecting biodiversity in flora and fauna (such as climate change, soil erosion, etc.).","pct":85}]}},"miscon":[{"grade":"Grade 8","subject":"Odia","qno":12,"pct":53,"chosen":"A","correct":"C","correct_pct":22,"stem":"ଜଙ୍ଗଲ କ୍ଷୟ ର ମୂଖ୍ୟ କାରଣ କଣ ହୋଇଛି?","opts":{"A":"ନୂଆଁ କାରଖାନା ଓ ଶିଳ୍ପ ଅଞ୍ଚଳ ସ୍ଥାପନ।","B":"ଜଙ୍ଗଲକୁ ଘରବାଡ଼ିରେ ପରିଣତ କରି ଶହର ବିସ୍ତାର।","C":"ଚାଷଜମି ବଢ଼ାଇବା ପାଇଁ ଜଙ୍ଗଲ ଶୁନ୍ୟ କରିବା","D":"ଜଙ୍ଗଲ ଅଞ୍ଚଳ ଭିତରକୁ ସଡ଼କ ବିକାଶ।"},"text":"Deforestation was blamed on factories and industry. The main cause is clearing forest to expand farmland.","skill":"By studying a subject, comprehend the concepts that may exist within it."},{"grade":"Grade 8","subject":"SST","qno":4,"pct":52,"chosen":"A","correct":"C","correct_pct":21,"stem":"ପାହାଡିଆ ଅଞ୍ଚଳରେ ବାନାଗ୍ନି ସାଧାରଣ କାରଣ କେଉଁଟି ?","opts":{"A":"ବିଜୁଳି ଦ୍ବାରା ଶୁଷ୍କ ଗଛରେ ନିଆଁ ଲାଗିବ।","B":"ପ୍ରାକୃତିକ ଢାଲୁ ନିଆଁ କୁ ବଢ଼ାଇବାରେ ସାହାଯ୍ୟ କରେ।","C":"ଲିଭି ନଥିବା ନିଆଁ କିମ୍ବା କ୍ୟାମ୍ପ ଅଗ୍ନି ରୁ ନିଆଁ ଲାଗିବ।","D":"ବୈଦ୍ୟୁତିକ ସ୍ପାର୍କ ରୁ ନିଆଁ ଲାଗିବ।"},"text":"Forest fires were blamed on lightning. The common cause in hilly areas is an unextinguished campfire, that is, human carelessness.","skill":"Explain the causes of forest fires, landslides, man-made disasters, and ways to mitigate disasters."},{"grade":"Grade 8","subject":"Maths","qno":2,"pct":41,"chosen":"C","correct":"A","correct_pct":17,"stem":"ଜଣେ ଶିକ୍ଷକଙ୍କର ୫ ଟି ଭିନ୍ନ ଭିନ୍ନ କାର୍ଡ ଅଛି: ♠ A, ♠2, ♠3, ♠4, ଏବଂ ♠5 ନିମ୍ନରେ ଦର୍ଶାଯାଇଛି । ସେ ବୋର୍ଡରେ ଗୋଟିଏ ଧାଡିରେ ଏହି କାର୍ଡଗୁଡ଼ିକ ମଧ୍ୟରୁ ୩ ଟି ସଜାଇବାକୁ ଚାହୁଁଛନ୍ତି। କେତୋଟି ଭିନ୍ନ ବ୍ୟବସ୍ଥା ସମ୍ଭବ ହେବ?","opts":{"A":"୬୦","B":"୧୦","C":"୬","D":"୧୨୦"},"text":"Children counted combinations instead of permutations, ignoring that the order of the cards matters.","skill":"Conduct an analysis of the basic concepts of permutation, combination, multiplication, and division in relation to the generalization of the methods."},{"grade":"Grade 5","subject":"EVS","qno":12,"pct":42,"chosen":"A","correct":"B","correct_pct":31,"stem":"On a cold night, Reena wrapped one plant in a plastic sheet and left another open. In the morning she saw water droplets only on the plastic sheet. Which process best explains this?","opts":{"A":"Evaporation","B":"Condensation","C":"Freezing","D":"Melting"},"text":"Children chose evaporation. The droplets form by condensation, water vapour turning to liquid on the cool sheet.","skill":"Identify situations related to various events, including estimating conditions (distance, weight, time duration) and using regional units of measurement (like yards, feet, miles) while establishing relationships between various causes and effects through simple techniques (examples - condensation, evaporation, separation, etc.) related to the lifespan of flowers, fruits, and other natural resources."},{"grade":"Grade 8","subject":"English","qno":12,"pct":39,"chosen":"B","correct":"C","correct_pct":29,"stem":"Which home action best mirrors banning old polluting vehicles?","opts":{"A":"Buy more vehicles for every individual at home","B":"Plant more trees in your neighbourhood","C":"Swap old devices for energy-saving ones","D":"Switch off lights and fans when not in use"},"text":"Children chose a generally 'green' action rather than the true parallel to scrapping old polluting vehicles, which is replacing old devices with energy-saving ones.","skill":"Compare between characters, events, ideas, themes and correlates them to their own life."},{"grade":"Grade 8","subject":"Odia","qno":8,"pct":39,"chosen":"B","correct":"A","correct_pct":32,"stem":"“କଲମର କାହାଣୀ” ଅନୁଛେଦ ଦ୍ୱାରା ମାନବ ପ୍ରଗତି ବିଷୟରେ କେଉଁ ବିଶାଳ ଧାରଣାକୁ ଉଦ୍ଧାର କରାଯାଇଛି?","opts":{"A":"ନିରନ୍ତର ନବୀନତା ଦିବାନିଶି ସମସ୍ୟା ସମାଧାନ କରି ଜୀବନକୁ ଭଲ କରିଥାଏ।","B":"ଆଧୁନିକ ପ୍ରଯୁକ୍ତିବିଦ୍ୟା  ସବୁ ପୁରୁଣା ଉଦ୍ଭାବନକୁ ସମ୍ପୂର୍ଣ୍ଣ ଭାବେ ପରିବର୍ତ୍ତନ କରେ।","C":"ନୂଆ ଉପକରଣ ତିଆରିରେ ସୃଜନଶୀଳତା ଠାରୁ ପାରମ୍ପରିକତା ଅଧିକ ମହତ୍ତ୍ୱପୂର୍ଣ୍ଣ।","D":"ଅଧିକାଂଶ ଉଦ୍ଭାବନ ଆକସ୍ମିକ ଭାବେ ଘଟେ ଓ ତାହାର କୌଣସି ଉଦ୍ଦେଶ୍ୟ ନଥାଏ।"},"text":"Children picked an absolute statement (new technology fully replaces the old) over the passage's nuanced idea that steady, ongoing innovation keeps improving life.","skill":"By studying a subject, comprehend the concepts that may exist within it."},{"grade":"Grade 8","subject":"English","qno":5,"pct":31,"chosen":"A","correct":"B","correct_pct":24,"stem":"Which event in the story shows the consequence of greed?","opts":{},"text":"Children chose the spilling of the honey pot (the trigger) over the real consequence of greed, the flies overindulging and getting trapped.","skill":"Compare between characters, events, ideas, themes and correlates them to their own life."},{"grade":"Grade 8","subject":"Science","qno":5,"pct":34,"chosen":"D","correct":"A","correct_pct":27,"stem":"ଜଣେ ଛାତ୍ର ଏକ ପରୀକ୍ଷଣ ବ୍ୟବହାର କରି ଯାଞ୍ଚ କରିବାକୁ ଚାହାଁନ୍ତି ଯେ ଏକ ସବୁଜ ପତ୍ର କ୍ଲୋରୋଫିଲ୍ ସାହାଯ୍ୟରେ ଖାଦ୍ୟ ପ୍ରସ୍ତୁତ କରିଛି କି ନାହିଁ । କେଉଁଟି ସୋପାନଗୁଡ଼ିକର ସଠିକ୍ କ୍ରମ ଅଟେ?","opts":{"A":"ପାଣିରେ ଫୁଟାନ୍ତୁ","B":"ଆୟୋଡିନ୍ ରେ ବୁଡ଼ାଇ ରଖନ୍ତୁ","C":"ଆଲକୋହଲରେ ଫୁଟାନ୍ତୁ","D":"ସୂର୍ଯ୍ୟକିରଣରେ ରଖନ୍ତୁ"},"text":"Children picked 'keep it in sunlight', confusing the plant's need for light with the starch-test procedure, which begins by boiling the leaf.","skill":"Simple techniques will be introduced to extract answers from asked questions. For instance, how to identify substances derived from colored flowers and how to determine whether green leaves contain chlorophyll."},{"grade":"Grade 8","subject":"English","qno":6,"pct":48,"chosen":"A","correct":"B","correct_pct":42,"stem":"Where does a sea turtle begin its life?","opts":{"A":"In the ocean","B":"On the beach","C":"Into small holes","D":"Inside the sea grass"},"text":"Children think a sea turtle's life begins in the ocean; it actually hatches on the beach. A read-from-text slip.","skill":"Identifies characters, main ideas and sequence of ideas and events in textual / non textual material"},{"grade":"Grade 8","subject":"Science","qno":11,"pct":36,"chosen":"C","correct":"B","correct_pct":30,"stem":"ଜଣେ ଡ୍ରାଇଭର ରାସ୍ତା ଉପରେ ଥିବା ପାଣିର ଖାଲରୁ ସୂର୍ଯ୍ୟର ଆଲୋକ ପ୍ରତିଫଳିତ ହେଉଥିବା ଦେଖିଲେ। ଏହି ପ୍ରତିଫଳନ କେଉଁ ନିୟମ ଦ୍ୱାରା ବ୍ୟାଖ୍ୟା ହୁଏ?","opts":{"A":"ଆଲୋକ ପାଣିରେ ପଡିବା ସମୟରେ ବକ୍ରିତ ହୁଏ","B":"ଆପତନ କୋଣ ଓ ପ୍ରତିଫଳନ କୋଣ ସମାନ ହୁଏ","C":"ଆଲୋକ ସମସ୍ତ ଦିଗକୁ ବିଛୁରିତ ହୋଇ ପଡ଼େ","D":"ଆଲୋକ ମାଟିରେ ପଡ଼ି ଶୋଷିତ ହୋଇଯାଏ"},"text":"Children chose 'light scatters in all directions' over the law of reflection, that the angle of incidence equals the angle of reflection.","skill":"Measure the angle of incidence and angle of reflection"}],"inputs":{"coverage":{"withData":0,"total":112}}}